@startuml C4_Ops_Monitoring
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Operations - Monitoring & Incident Response

Boundary(monitoring, "Monitoring Stack") {
    Component(prometheus, "Prometheus", "Metrics", "Time-series DB")
    Component(grafana, "Grafana", "Visualization", "Dashboards")
    Component(jaeger, "Jaeger", "Tracing", "Distributed traces")
    Component(elasticsearch, "Elasticsearch", "Logs", "Log aggregation")
}

Boundary(alerting, "Alerting & Escalation") {
    Component(alert_rules, "AlertRules", "Thresholds", "CPU >80%, latency >100ms")
    Component(alert_manager, "AlertManager", "Logic", "Alert routing")
    Component(pagerduty, "PagerDuty", "On-call", "Incident escalation")
    Component(notifications, "Notifications", "Delivery", "Slack/Email/SMS")
}

Boundary(dashboards, "Dashboards") {
    Component(health_dash, "HealthDashboard", "Overview", "System health")
    Component(perf_dash, "PerformanceDashboard", "Metrics", "Throughput/latency")
    Component(trace_dash, "TraceDashboard", "Traces", "Request flow")
    Component(log_dash, "LogDashboard", "Logs", "Error investigation")
}

Boundary(incident_response, "Incident Response") {
    Component(incident_detection, "IncidentDetection", "Alert", "Alert triggered")
    Component(runbook, "Runbook", "Procedures", "Troubleshooting steps")
    Component(remediation, "Remediation", "Action", "Fix the issue")
    Component(postmortem, "PostMortem", "Learning", "Root cause analysis")
}

prometheus --> grafana: Powers
prometheus --> alert_rules: Evaluates
alert_rules --> alert_manager: Triggers
alert_manager --> pagerduty: Escalates
pagerduty --> notifications: Sends

prometheus --> health_dash: Data for
jaeger --> trace_dash: Data for
elasticsearch --> log_dash: Data for

incident_detection --> runbook: Consults
runbook --> remediation: Guides
remediation --> postmortem: Documents

Note as N1
Monitoring Objectives:
1. Detect anomalies early
2. Alert on SLA violation
3. Enable rapid investigation
4. Automate common fixes
5. Learn from incidents

Key Metrics:
- Latency (p50, p95, p99)
- Error rate (%)
- Throughput (tasks/sec)
- Resource utilization (CPU, Memory)

Alert Thresholds:
- Latency >100ms (warning), >1s (critical)
- Error rate >5% (warning), >10% (critical)
- CPU >80% (warning), >95% (critical)

Response Time Target: <5 minutes to incident resolution
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
